{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Strobe",
  "description": "Strobe is a beat-synced brightness modulator, decomposed from the legacy fused kernel into two reusable pieces: a beat-gated square wave and a brightness flash effect.\n\nThe source image flows into the flash node, which modulates it by a brightness envelope driven by the beat gate. The beat gate reads FrameTime.beats and produces a square wave at a synced rate (1/1 to 1/64), scaled by the amount slider. The gate is held internally at 50 percent duty cycle and zero phase, giving a clean on/off pulse matching the legacy strobe behavior.\n\n§8 param triggers: a second path reads generator_input.trigger_count (the layer's clip-edge + audio-trigger effective count, D5) through a Trigger Gate node whose enable is bound to the Clip Trigger toggle card (isTriggerGate) - when on, each new count snaps an Envelope Decay node to full brightness which decays exponentially back to zero. A Math (Max) node combines this trigger flash with the beat gate's square wave before driving the flash node's amount, so a kick and a beat-tick both read as a flash, whichever is brighter this frame. Reachability proof for §8 D6/D5: this is the only shipped effect with a clip_trigger card.\n\nThe flash node applies the combined gate signal to the image in one of three modes: Opacity fades toward black, White fades toward white, and Gain applies a 3x brighten. The result is driven directly to the output.\n\nNo grouping is needed: the graph is already transparent, and moving between nodes requires no layering.",
